method.name: emulation_pim_config
method.description: This procedure will configure PIM SM interface.

description.text: This option defines the action to be taken. Limitations: for modify mode, the following options cannot be changed: router_id, dr_priority, join_prune_holdtime, and join_prune_interval. Valid options are: create (DEFAULT) modify delete disable enable
PIM-SM handle if the option -mode is not create.

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.
Supports SM (sparse mode) and SSM (source spefic multicast). (DEFAULT = sm)
Type of the PIM session router. Supports remote_rp type only. c_rp and c_bsr types are not supported.
The IP version of the interface. Choices are: 4, 6 (DEFAULT = 4)
If 1, enables the PIM-SM interface to participate in Bootstrap Router election procedure. Valid choices are: 0 - disable 1 - enable (DEFAULT = 0)
If 1, enables support for unicast trasmission in Bootstrap procedure. Valid choices are: 0 - disable 1 - enable (DEFAULT = 1)
Hash Mask Length of the Bootstrap Router (BSR) that is set with the same name in all Bootstrap Messages sent by this BSR.
The time interval (in seconds) between two consecutive bootstrap messages sent by the BSR. (DEFAULT = 60)
Priority of the Bootstrap Router (BSR) that is set with the same name in all Bootstrap Messages sent by this BSR. (DEFAULT = 64)

Amount of time (in seconds) of not receiving any Bootstrap Messages, after which the BSR if candidate at that point of time will decide that the currently elected BSR has gone down and will restart BSR election procedure. (DEFAULT = 130)

Number of PIM-SM sessions to create on the interface. If this parameter is 1 then the default behaviour of this function is to create a router and add the <interface_handle> interfaces to it. In this case the following parameters may be lists: interface_handle ip_version generation_id_mode hello_holdtime hello_interval prune_delay prune_delay_tbit override_interval bidir_capable send_generation_id prune_delay_enable neighbor_intf_ip_addr bootstrap_support_unicast bootstrap_enable bootstrap_hash_mask_len bootstrap_interval bootstrap_priority bootstrap_timeout (only IxTclNetwork api) (DEFAULT = 1)
The interface IP address.
The interface IP address octet to be incremented by given step.
The prefix length on the interface (DEFAULT = 24). NOTE: This value is being maintained for backwards compatibility and shouldn't be used going forward. Please use the -intf_ip_prefix_len value.
The prefix length on the interface. (DEFAULT = 24)
Enable learning of elected BSR and Candidate RPs. (DEFAULT = 1)
Discard the learnt BSR and Candidate RP info. (DEFAULT = 0)
The ID of the router in IPv4 format. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.1)
The value use to increment the router_id when count > 1. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.1)
The gateway IP address of the port interface. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.0)
The gateway IP address octet to be incremented by given step. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.1)
Auto pick Neighbor
The interface IP address of PIM-SM neighbor (next hop). (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.0)
The interface IP address step for the PIM-SM neighbor. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.0)
The Designated Router (DR) priority assigned to this simulated router. (DEFAULT = 0)
If true (1), enable bi-directional PIM. (DEFAULT = 0)
Hello interval in seconds. (DEFAULT = 30)
The length of time, in seconds, between the transmission of Hello messages. (DEFAULT = 105)
The length of time, in seconds, between transmission of Join/Prune messages. Also called t_periodic in RFCs. (DEFAULT = 60)

The period, in seconds, during which a router receiving a Join/Prune must keep the state alive. The default is 3 times the Join/Prune interval. If this value is 65536 (0xffff), then the timeout is infinite and if this value isi 0, the timeout is immediate. (DEFAULT = 180)
If true (1), the LAN prune propagation delay is enabled for this interface. (DEFAULT = 0)

The value, in milliseconds, of the LAN prune propagation delay for this interface. It indicates to an upstream router how long to wait for a Join override message before it prunes an interface. (DEFAULT = 500)
The delay interval, in milliseconds, for randomizing the transmission time for override messages, which are used when scheduling a delayed Join message. (DEFAULT = 2500)
If VLAN is enable on the Ixia interface, this option will configure the VLAN number. RANGE 0-4095. (DEFAULT = 100)
If the user configures more than one interface on the Ixia with VLAN, he can choose to automatically increment the VLAN tag or leave it idle for each interface. (DEFAULT = increment)

If the -vlan_id_mode is increment, this will be the step value by which the VLAN tags are incremented. RANGE 0-4095 When vlan_id_step causes the vlan_id value to exceed it's maximum value the increment will be done modulo <number of possible vlan ids>. Examples: vlan_id = 4094; vlan_id_step = 2 -> new vlan_id value = 0 vlan_id = 4095; vlan_id_step = 11 -> new vlan_id value = 10 (DEFAULT = 1)
VLAN user priority assigned to emulated router node. RANGE 0-7 (DEFAULT = 0)
If this option is present, all the Pim Interface and router in the given device group are deleted.
The mode used for creating the 32-bit value for the Generation Identifier (GenID) option in Hello messages. Valid options are: increment random constant

If true (1), the T flag bit in the LAN Prune Delay option of the Hello message is set (= 1). Setting this bit specifies that the sending PIM-SM router has the ability to disable Join message suppression.
If true (1), the generation ID is included in Hello messages.
The MAC address of the directly connected interface.
The incrementing step for the MAC address of the interface. Valid only when IxNetwork Tcl API is used. (DEFAULT = 0000.0000.0001)

Enables vlan on the directly connected PIM router interface. Valid options are: 0 - disable, 1 - enable. This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is a PIM router handle. This option is available only when IxNetwork tcl API is used. (DEFAULT = 0)
Name of Pim interface stack in the scenario.
Flag.

Force Semantic
Flag.
Name of Pim Router stack in the scenario.
Number of Join/Prunes
Number of Sources
Number of C-RP Ranges
Enable or disable BFD registration.

If this parameter is > 0 and gre_enable is '0' the router interfaces will be the loopback protocol interfaces. The number of loopback interfaces will be count * loopback_count. Valid only when: IxTclProtocols HLTSET and loopback_count > 0 and mode create and mvpn_enable 0 and interface_handle missing.
Valid only when: IxTclProtocols HLTSET and loopback_count > 0 and mode create and mvpn_enable 0 and interface_handle missing.

The step used to increment the 'loopback_ip_address' when moving from one loopback interface to the next. Valid only when: IxTclProtocols HLTSET and loopback_count > 1 and mode create and mvpn_enable 0 and interface_handle missing.

notes.note: 1) MVPN parameters are not supported with IxTclNetwork API (new API). If the current session or command was run with -return_detailed_handles 0 the following keys will be omitted from the command response: handle, interfaces

examples.example: See files starting with PIM_ in the Samples subdirectory. Also see some of the MVPN sample files for further examples of the PIM usage. See the PIM example in Appendix A, "Example APIs," for one specific example usage.
